{
  "texts": [
    "Jerome's involvement, let us imagine, makes a difference to the output: the painting would be different if Jerome was not there, and it might be difficult to replace Jerome.",
    "Jerome hence scores highly for relevance/non-redundancy.",
    "Lastly, consider Jake making a solo attempt to produce an image of a 'cat on a mat' using Stable Diffusion.",
    "Take away his access to the system, and Jake would fail to produce the image, because he lacks relevant skills to make it another way.",
    "Generally, the more relevant and non-redundant a contribution, the stronger the claim to inclusion in a co-creating collective."
  ]
}